The solar-powered, trail-ready, smartphone-charging weather alert radio


Product Information

 The Eton Raptor Solar Charge Emergency Radio is a radio, cell phone charger, weather alert and more, all wrapped up into one product. Not only does the Eton Raptor tell you the basics of your journey, but it can also take pressure readings so you can be aware of changing weather, tell you how high you've climbed, and it can wake you up in the morning so you can continue your trek. When it gets too dark to continue, enjoy local AM and FM radio stations or use its flashlight to find your supper. It even has a bottle opener so you can crack open a cold one and relax. title: For Sale:  AR500 targets with "stands", just the C zone of USPSA target
location: near Belleville, IL actually, St. Louis, Missouri
postcontent:
These are 3/8ths thick AR500 steel targets.  If you are familiar with either a USPSA target or an IDPA target, cut off the D zone of the USPSA target or the down 3 zone of an IDPA target and this is what you get.  See pic below.

This is about my 4th generation of targets built.  To keep prices low, I make all my stuff so it fits in a USPS flat rate box meant for board games.  So these plates are about 11.75" wide and about 23.75" long.

These are meant for guys to mainly practice with their handguns, especially for the IDPA classifier stage where the targets are height adjustable to 6 foot tall, then 4 foot, and then 5 foot.

There is one catch though.  The legs....You supply them.  1/2" diameter rebar works just fine, and you can buy it in 4 foot lengths at any Home Depot or Lowe's or Menards.  Each 4 foot length of rebar is about $3.00 at those stores.  So you spend an extra $10 dollars or so out the door for a complete target plate and stand set up.

Confused yet?

Sorry.  If you have any questions, you can just email me, too.

Here is a video of me shooting the Mark I version in August of last year.  (Yes, that is actually me shooting, and NO!  I didn't do anything funny to speed up the video):

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-WpLA0J8mO0

It is $400 for a set of 3 shipped.

OR $145 shipped for just one.

It is just a rattle can spray paint job.

Be sure to follow your typical range safety precautions like ear protection and definitely eye protection with these.
